# PCManFM Mini Desk

This is a modified version of PCManFM 1.4.0, altered to create a mini desktop with the default features hidden. It can be used as a small desktop, for example, 360x640, instead of full screen (--desktop). You can drag and drop files into the ~/Desktop folder.

# Hiding menubar
PCManFM patch for hiding menubar toggle (GTK2 version), accessed via 'View' menu or pressing Ctrl+m
https://gist.github.com/M4he/3a8171a7f39d9ba9a0cf6bb387b08061

# Setting hide as default setting
https://github.com/lxde/pcmanfm/issues/22

Side Pane (F9)
Toolbar
Statusbar (Ctrl+b)
Menubar (Ctrl+m)



